The fuck are you talking about? Zombies are pretty low risk all things considered and they’re great for easy ammo.
On higher difficulties enemies can kill you much faster because you have a lowered natural damage resistance and no one shot protection. On higher difficulties loot from corpses is also lower. This means you have to spend all your money on ammo, meaning no better gear, or you have to find a way to get ammo easy. Zombies are easy to kill, low threat, and don’t take much ammo to kill. Sometimes they rucking g kill themselves even.
While zombies don’t have a lot of loot, and higher difficulties lower it more, the amount of bodies makes up for that. Also the fact that each gun they carry has the potential to have up to a full magazine of ammo.
Zombies don’t make you money, they let you keep your already existing money. For better things.
